
[Annapolis, 18 Jan. 1784. Entry in SJL reads: Short. P. C. [Peter Carr] disapproving Wmsbgapproving Jmscy [James City] but query as to healthfulnessrefer to himsubject in cypherNicholashealth better. Not found. TJ evidently enclosed in this letter a cipher based on the word Nicholas, a cipher he used in subsequent letters to Short. In an undated extract of his letter of 30 Apr. 1784, he sent Short another copy of the same code. See also TJ to Short, 1 Mch. 1784.]
